Invite a classmate or friend to collaborate on your repository. 
Ask them to fork your repository, make a change, and create a pull request. 
Accept their pull request, and explain the collaborative process


->Forking: Your collaborator forks (copies) your repository to their own GitHub account. This allows them to make changes without affecting your original repository.
->Cloning: Your collaborator clones the forked repository to their local machine to work on it.
->Making Changes: Your collaborator makes changes locally and commits them.
->Pushing Changes: They push the committed changes to their forked repository on GitHub.
->Creating a Pull Request: Your collaborator creates a pull request to propose their changes to your original repository.
->Reviewing and Merging: You review the changes in the pull request. If you approve, you merge the changes into your repository.
